HEADWORD: Anti-Semitism
<hw>An`ti-Sem"i*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Opposition
to, or hatred of, Semites, esp. Jews. The word is sometimes also applied
to acts motivated by or evincing antisemitism.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>An`ti-Sem"ite</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> --
<wf>An`ti-Sem*it"ic</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

